result.name: 珠江酒家

reviews.text:
Old times deco,  friendly staff, neat manual,  and only by looking from the outside of the shop,  we were surprised when we walked in on an ordinary weekday early evening looking for a table for two,  we were told they were quite fully booked.   Honestly we did not expect this shop at such location to be doing such well,  and our expectation was so totally biased we then realized.

They serve quite a varieties of dishes,  I guess it can be safely assumed it is the taste of southern China.   The dishes tend to be on the richer side of flavour,  as I tasted and saw there they are delicately prepared and in good portion.   Plain rice is steamed properly, which is not too common nowadays.

Staff are efficient and friendly.   For those who like the "comfort" and "cleaniness" of shopping mall may not like the location and deco but to me it is a proper bistro,  the vibe is just right.

Big group remember to book.  
Drivers can easily park on the nearby street.
Cash only.
No service charge.
Booking recommended.

So good traditional Guangdong style, better say Chiu Chow style dinner place.  Need to book and reserve a table and worth to wait!  The fried small oyster is amazing!   Sweat and sour pork definitely top 3 in HK.
Very tasty food and reasonable price.  Chu Kong has dishes that you cannot easily find in other canton cuisine restaurant.  Lamb brisket, pork fat curb fry veggie, cold spicy clams.
The soup was good but all the other dishes were just so-so.
Though the decor is old, they serve tasty food at a competitive price

本是傳統酒家 但菜式突破傳統！混合中西東南亞味道

蝴蝶腩 一陣尿騷味 好明顯係處理不當 向侍應查詢味道為何如此怪 侍應竟然話 係咁㗎啦食多幾嚿就慣

其他出品都是麻麻，質素不好，而且等了一小時才上菜

不會再吃

第二次來到了珠江酒家，環境格局依舊，人物依舊，來這裏懷舊一下，正好。

中式懷舊的酒家在香港已買少見少，我們點了蠔爽、黃金墨魚咀。胡椒豬肚湯、椒鹽鵝腸、涼拌花甲，都是這裏的招牌菜。

花甲肥美，鵝腸惹味。胡椒豬肚湯夠暖身，黒魚咀香口、蠔爽飽滿，每樣都保持水準。

點了可樂和啤酒，這樣一坐便坐了3個多小時，大家食得盡興又開心。這裏，還是會再來的！
